HEADWORD: Torqued
<hw>Torqued</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>torquere</ets> to twist, to turn, to wind.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Wreathed; twisted.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Twisted; bent; -- said of a
dolphin haurient, which forms a figure like the letter S.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torques</ent>⟦br⟧
